Five killed in Burundi attack - army . Five civilians were killed on Tuesday night when rebels attacked a northern suburb of the capital Bujumbura , an army spokesman said on Wednesday . Lieutenant - Colonel Isaie Nibizi gave no further details on the attack in Kinama neighbourhood . " The rebels killed five people in Kinama last night . The army intervened and chased the rebels , " he said . Some 150 , 000 people have died in ethnic violence in Burundi since 1993 after Tutsi soldiers murdered the first freely - elected President Melchior Ndadaye , a Hutu . 
